summary: When I woke up this morning I weighed 145.8lbs.The heaviest I let myself get to was 153lbs. The healthiest weight for me...
body: When I woke up this morning I weighed 145.8lbs.The heaviest I let myself get to was 153lbs. The healthiest weight for me personally would be about 125-130lbs. Though I’ve been working at this for about a month and a half and my progress may not seem too linear or fast (not to mention that I still have about 20lbs to go), this is not something I could have ever even imagined being possible. The struggle for me used to be to gain weight. Then it felt like once I started, I couldn’t stop. After reaching my highest weight, I felt doomed. If I’m only 23 and this unhealthy, how am I going to be at 30? 40? 50+? Changing my lifestyle felt impossible. Slowly but surely I have started working out (with a goal of at least 2x a week to begin) and trying to cut back on sugar, carbs, fat, and sodium. Some weeks I haven’t gone to the gym, others I’ve gone 4-5 times a week. Some weeks I have had 1-2 cheat days, surpassing my appropriate calorie intake, others I could’ve eaten more. I’m not perfect and no expert at this, but the point is I made a goal and I’m slowly trying to work at it. More importantly, I’m seeing results, no matter how slowly or tiny. And that has made all the difference for me
